name: Franklin Western Asset Core Plus Bond Fund
longDescription: In pursuing its investment objective, the underlying fund will generally invest at least 80 percent of its assets in debt instruments of issuers anywhere in the world; may invest in Mainland China through the Bond Connect or directly; may invest in debt instruments of any maturity, but will normally maintain a portfolio whose average effective duration is within 30 percent of the average duration of the U.S. bond market as a whole, as estimated by the funds sub-advisor. Franklin Western Asset Core Plus Bond Active ETF seeks to maximize total return through exposure to investmentgrade debt instruments.
